Subject: 26th Armoured Brigade (United Kingdom) 
To: Angus
Content:
The 26th Armoured Brigade was part of the British Army during the Second World War. This brigade was converted from the British 1st Motor Machine Gun Brigade on October 12, 1940, it served with British 6th Armoured Division during the North African Campaign and then through the Italian Campaign. During this time it was briefly attached to the British 4th Infantry Division and the British 78th Infantry Division.
